						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in the boundary between Irikapalli and Gāmālapāḍu.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Phālguṇa, śu. 15, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land for conducting services and worship by a certain Guṇḍaya-Raḍḍi. There is a reference to the waiving of tax <hi rend="italic">(pannu)</hi> and tolls <hi rend="italic">(sunkam).</hi> In characters of the 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
